Industry Context

This is a common Tier 1 Service Desk incident following operating system or feature updates. Display flickering and graphical artifacts often indicate a graphics driver compatibility issue rather than a hardware failure, particularly when the problem affects multiple displays simultaneously. Service desk technicians should verify pending driver updates before escalating to desktop support or replacing hardware. Confirming the display functions correctly after the driver installation and restart is essential before resolving the incident.
